Yes. In Tapis apps you can give parameters default values.

They are typically expressed as environment variables in the app definition, under `envVariables`. Each entry is a JSON object, and the `value` field is the default:

```json
"envVariables": [
  {
    "key": "MY_PARAM",
    "value": "default_value",
    "description": "Some parameter with a default"
  },
  {
    "key": "_tapisAppId",
    "value": "my-app",
    "description": "Default app id"
  },
  {
    "key": "_tapisAppVersion",
    "value": "0.0.1",
    "description": "Default app version"
  }
]
```

At runtime, if the user/job doesn’t override `MY_PARAM`, the app sees `default_value` as the value of that parameter.
